body:
`typedef`-ing a parameterized class inside a parameterized submodule causes an assertion failure in `V3Broken.cpp`.

To reproduce, compile the following code with ``verilator --debug-check --trace --exe --build -j `nproc` --binary trigger_assertion.sv -o trigger_assertion`` (using the git master version):

```systemverilog
class cls #(parameter int PARAM = 0);
endclass

module submod #(
    parameter int P
) ();
    typedef cls #(
        .PARAM(P) // does not neccessarily have to be P, can also be a constant
    ) cls_t;
endmodule;

module top ();
    submod #(
        .P(42)
    ) i_submod ();
endmodule
```

The following assertion failure will show up:
```
%Error: Internal Error: trigger_assertion.sv:7:13: ../V3Broken.cpp:168: Broken link in node (or something without maybePointedTo): 'm_classp && !m_classp->brokeExists()' @ ./V3Ast__gen_impl.h:969
                                                 : ... note: In instance 'top.i_submod'
    7 |     typedef cls #(
      |             ^~~
                        ... See the manual at https://verilator.org/verilator_doc.html for more assistance.
```

Interestingly, note that
```systemverilog
// (typedef not in submodule)

class cls #(parameter int PARAM = 0);
endclass

module top();
    typedef cls #(.PARAM(42)) cls_t;
endmodule
```
does not trigger the assertion failure, nor does

```systemverilog
// (submodule without parameters)

class cls #(parameter int PARAM = 0);
endclass

module submod ();
    typedef cls #(
        .PARAM(42)
    ) cls_t;
endmodule;

module top ();
    submod i_submod ();
endmodule
```
